<br>
I personally like to get my pet low and jump in with a fear to get rid of the rest and melee the formar pet... ( also works if you're charm kiting 1 on 1, and your &quot;PET&quot; is loosing )...but of course, chant kiting the almost dead one is much safer.<br>
<br>
Fear kite is fun...if you're below lvl 47, the Kodiak cave directly beneath Velks is KILLER! They hardly ever resist ( even Icetooth ) and the *coughpathingcough* is nice. I suggest pulling with snare...fear ( time it so you don't get hit. hehe ) and haste ( whichever you have...if you're grouped, do that, else do jonathan's whatever is best )<br>
<br>
Not much loot there, but damn good xp.<br>
<br>
I just got my AoE snare, and thought I'd try quad fearing, don't do it. Way too hard to control the mob's. Was a good idea though, and if anyone has figured out how to do it, please tell me, because it seems WAY too fun to pass up. <p><select size = "1" name = "selCharacter">
